strings.Value: "The duel's over. Valerie is the winner."
"The duel's not over until one of the participants is dead."
"Fredero did it! That scoundrel!"
"Let me heal you."
"Oh no! Your beautiful face!"
{n}Fredero kneels heavily on one knee, wheezing and spluttering.{/n} "Right... You always were better... at fighting than... at evolving your spirit and character..."
{n}Valerie stands over her defeated adversary, gripping her weapon. She momentarily takes her eyes off Fredero, bent low before her, and looks to you.{/n}

{n}Fredero steps back and sheathes his weapon.{/n} "Looks like everything's in its place, doesn't it? You could be however insolent to whomever you wanted, as long as you were considered as a girl, Valerie... but now you'll have to answer for all the stupid things you said in pride or heated moments."

"I'm satisfied with the outcome of this duel. I see no reasons to linger here, upsetting the owners of this trading post and the {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}. With great sadness, I will continue my way without Valerie, who from now on has no right to return to the Order of {g|Shelyn}the Eternal Rose{/g} due to her transgressions."
"I will bother you no longer. My regards, Your Grace. Valerie..." {n}Fredero stops short.{/n} "Farewell."
{n}Valerie lowers her weapon with obvious relief.{/n} "Enough, Fredero. You got what you wanted. Leave the lands of the {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}... and my life. Forever."
"Dear gods... Your face, Valerie!"
"What? Is there something..." {n}Valerie touches the wound crossing her face and looks at the blood on her fingers — more baffled than scared.{/n}
{n}Valerie shakes her head.{/n} "Strange... I do not remember receiving this blow. Not at all..."

{n}Valerie wipes her fingers on the hem of her clothes with disdain.{/n} "Please, {name}! I have not yet had a chance to rest after Fredero's doleful outpourings about my precious beauty — do not echo him!"

{n}She touches the wound again, winces, and finally waves it off.{/n} "It is nothing. I do not even feel any pain. Only fatigue. Save your pity for someone who is truly wounded. And I... just need to rest. And wash myself clean after all these conversations about {g|Shelyn}Shelyn{/g}."
"Praise {g|Sarenrae}Sarenrae{/g}, the battle finished without any victims! Right? That was it?"
"Too much talk. Enough. Leave her."
"Yikes! That sliced good!"
"You don't show fear to the lowborn... Worthy behavior."
